      "span_text": "The membranes were blocked with 5% nonfat dry-milk in a buffer (10 mM Tris-HCL [pH 7.6], 100 mM NaCl, and 0.1% Tween 20) for 1 h at room temperature, incubated with the desired primary antibodies overnight at 4 ∘ C and then incubated with alkaline phosphatase-conjugated goat anti-rabbit secondary antibodies at a 1: 1000 dilution for 1 h at room temperature as previously described"
